name: Build Table
Plot 60 days of COVID infections
How to find County geocoordinates
info:
I wanted to build an app that reports Covid-19 data by state / county.  I went on a long hunt to find an API that would return all counties in a state.  The best I could come up with is parsing the data from this wikipedia page...
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:Michael_J/County_table 

- Edit the wikipedia page
- Just copy the contents
- Save the contents as a local file allcounties.txt
- Cancel out of the wikipedia page edit.

On my Linux system, I grabbed three columns [ County name, Latitude, Longitude ], then cleaned it up.  
Here's the pipeline of commands
- cat the file
- cut columns 13,42,45
- remove the degree symbol
- remove extraneous [ characters
- grep on the + to give you all counties in USA
- 3049 rows of data
- grep on the State you are interested in
- replace | with commas
- remove the +
- replace the unicode – with a normal dash - (the API expects a - minus longitude)
- Copy the 21 counties in NJ into the template node


$ cat allcounties.txt | cut -d\| -f13,42,45 | tr -d '°' | tr -d '[' | grep "+" | grep "New Jersey" | sed -e 's/|/,/g' | sed -e 's/+//g' | sed -e 's/–/-/g'
